com.poesys.db.dao
Interface IDaoFactory<T extends IDbDto>

Type Parameters:
T - the type of IDbDto that the DAOs handle
All Known Implementing Classes:
DaoCacheFactory, DaoDirectFactory, DaoMemcachedFactory
public interface IDaoFactory<T extends IDbDto>

An interface for a generic data access object (DAO) factory. The IDaoFactory lets you generate a DAO object appropriate to your desired framework.

Author:
Robert J. Muller

getQueryList

IQueryList<T> getQueryList(IQuerySql<T> sql,
                           int rows)
Generate a QueryList DAO that queries a list of objects using a non-parameterized SQL query specification. Set the number of rows to allow fetching more than one row at a time, usually to a value that trades off memory use and network access.

Parameters:
sql - the SQL query specification
rows - the number of rows to fetch at once, optimizes the query
Returns:
the query DAO

Generate a QueryListWithParameters DAO that queries a list of objects based on a set of parameters using a SQL query specification that contains parameters and parameter-binding capabilities.

Type Parameters:
S - the type of IDbDto that contains parameters

the query DAO

getInsert

IInsert<T> getInsert(IInsertSql<T> sql,
                     java.lang.Boolean key)
Generate an IInsert DAO that inserts a single object using a SQL insert specification. The DAO may generate a key as specified if the object has an identity primary key. The database generates the key, then the DAO retrieves it using the key-retrieval feature of JDBC.

Parameters:
sql - the SQL INSERT specification
key - true if you want to supply a key, false if the database management system generates the key and JDBC returns it separately
Returns:
the insert DAO

getInsertBatch

IInsertBatch<T> getInsertBatch(IInsertSql<T> sql)
Generate an IInsertBatch DAO that inserts a batched list of objects using a SQL insert specification. The batch processing does not enable key generation through identity keys.

Parameters:
sql - the SQL INSERT specification
Returns:
the insert DAO

getInsertCollection

IInsertCollection<T> getInsertCollection(IInsertSql<T> sql,
                                         java.lang.Boolean key)
Generate an IInsertCollection DAO that inserts a collection of objects using a SQL insert specification. The DAO may generate keys as specified if the object has an identity primary key.

Parameters:
sql - the SQL INSERT specification
key - true if you want to supply a key, false if you want the key generated (identity keys)
Returns:
the insert DAO
